Profile Created: Turbo Funk
Description: A modern, experimental profile designed to pull bright, funky shots with a lighter body. It uses a long bloom phase to develop unique flavors and a declining pressure ramp for a quick, clean extraction.
Preparation: 18g dose, ground medium-fine. Target a 1:2 ratio (36g output) at 92°C. Total shot time should be around 25-30 seconds, including pre-infusion and bloom.
Why This Works: The initial low-flow pre-infusion and extended bloom allow the coffee to saturate evenly and develop complex acidity and funky, fermented notes, especially with light roasts. The subsequent "Turbo Charge" phase uses a declining pressure profile to maintain a high flow rate, extracting sweetness while keeping the body light and avoiding bitterness.
Special Notes: Best suited for light roast, naturally processed coffees. A paper filter on the bottom of the portafilter can help enhance clarity.

