Profile Created: Fruity Funk Fusion
Description: A multi-stage profile designed to highlight the wild, fruity, and funky notes in light roast coffees. It uses a long, gentle pre-infusion and a blooming phase to develop complex aromatics, followed by a declining pressure phase to ensure a sweet, clean finish with a lighter body.
Preparation: Dose 18g of a light roast coffee, ground slightly coarser than a typical espresso setting. Target a final liquid weight of 45g. Temperature is set to 92°C. Total shot time should be around 45-55 seconds, including the pre-infusion and bloom.
Why This Works: The extended 15-second low-flow pre-infusion and 10-second zero-flow bloom gently saturate the puck, extracting delicate, volatile compounds without pulling harsh bitters. The declining pressure from 8 to 6 bars during the main extraction prevents over-extraction, reducing bitterness and promoting a sweet, thin-bodied cup that lets the funky fruit notes shine.
Special Notes: A paper filter at the bottom of the basket is recommended to enhance clarity and prevent stalling with finer grinds.

